==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sprit
<hw>Sprit</hw> <pr>(spr⟦icr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Akin to G.
<ets>spritzen</ets>, <ets>spr⟦uum⟧tzen</ets>. See <er>Sprit</er>,
<pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>To throw out with force from a narrow
orifice; to eject; to spurt out.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir
T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sprit
<hw>Sprit</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>spryttan</ets> to
sprout, bud. See <er>Sprout</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>, and cf.
<er>Spurt</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, <er>Sprit</er> a spar.]</ety> <def>To
sprout; to bud; to germinate, as barley steeped for malt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sprit
<hw>Sprit</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shoot; a sprout.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Sprit
<hw>Sprit</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>spret</ets>, AS.
<ets>spre⟦oacute⟧t</ets> a sprit; spear; akin to D. <ets>spriet</ets>,
and E. <ets>sprout</ets>, <ets>sprit</ets>, v.t. & i. See
<er>Sprout</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A small
boom, pole, or spar, which crosses the sail of a boat diagonally from
the mast to the upper aftmost corner, which it is used to extend and
elevate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprite</ent>⟦br⟧
